{"schema_version":"1.6.0","id":"OESA-2022-1502","modified":"2022-01-27T11:31:14Z","published":"2022-01-27T11:31:14Z","related":["CVE-2021-4034"],"summary":"polkit security update","details":"Define and Handle authorizations tool.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nA local privilege escalation vulnerability was found on polkit&apos;s pkexec utility. The pkexec application is a setuid tool designed to allow unprivileged users to run commands as privileged users according predefined policies. The current version of pkexec doesn&apos;t handle the calling parameters count correctly and ends trying to execute environment variables as commands. An attacker can leverage this by crafting environment variables in such a way it&apos;ll induce pkexec to execute arbitrary code. When successfully executed the attack can cause a local privilege escalation given unprivileged users administrative rights on the target machine.(CVE-2021-4034)","affected":[{"package":{"ecosystem":"openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1","name":"polkit","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/polkit&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0","fixed":"0.116-8.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["polkit-debugsource-0.116-8.oe1.aarch64.rpm","polkit-libs-0.116-8.oe1.aarch64.rpm","polkit-devel-0.116-8.oe1.aarch64.rpm","polkit-debuginfo-0.116-8.oe1.aarch64.rpm","polkit-0.116-8.oe1.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["polkit-help-0.116-8.oe1.noarch.rpm"],"src":["polkit-0.116-8.oe1.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["polkit-0.116-8.oe1.x86_64.rpm","polkit-debuginfo-0.116-8.oe1.x86_64.rpm","polkit-debugsource-0.116-8.oe1.x86_64.rpm","polkit-libs-0.116-8.oe1.x86_64.rpm","polkit-devel-0.116-8.oe1.x86_64.rpm"]}},{"package":{"ecosystem":"openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2","name":"polkit","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/polkit&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0","fixed":"0.116-9.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["polkit-debuginfo-0.116-9.oe1.aarch64.rpm","polkit-devel-0.116-9